FBIS3-36605 "drsov026_s_94001" FBIS-SOV-94-026 Document Type:Daily Report 8 Feb 1994 Georgia U.S. Diplomat's Killer Sentenced to 15 Years LD0702184594 Tbilisi First Program Television Network in Georgian 1700 GMT 7 Feb 94 LD0702184594 Tbilisi First Program Television Network Language: Georgian Article Type:BFN [Summary] The Georgian Supreme Court today sentenced the killer of Fred Woodruff, a U.S. diplomat attached to the U.S. embassy in Tbilisi, to 15 years' imprisonment . In an incident that took place on a highway near Tbilisi on 8 August 1993, a private in the Georgian Defense Ministry's 3d battalion, Anzor Sharmaidze, fired at a passing car carrying Woodruff, killing the American on the spot.
